This paper proposes a novel approach for support vector regression that addresses two challenging issues in machine learning: noisy data and dealing with different distributions of boundary data. These issues are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and statistical learning (cs.SI). The use of dual coordinate descent and stochastic gradient descent also suggests relevance to optimization and algorithms (cs.DS), while the focus on regression and prediction aligns with work in neural networks (cs.NE).
